observations.recommendation:
We recommended that Management:
a. Timely submits copies of MOA or Trust Agreement and other contracts to the Office of the Municipal Accountant and the Auditor for all funds transferred to the Municipality;
b. Require the Accounting Office to maintain Subsidiary Ledgers to record in detail the different balances of Due to NGAs and projects for a proper disposition of fund transfer to LGU.

We recommended that the Municipal Treasurer immediately restitute/deposit the missing funds totaling P1,867,072.57;
Likewise, the Municipal Mayor shall:
a) Cause the withholding of the Municipal Treasurer’s salaries and other monies due to her;
b)  Relieve her of her duties as liquidating officer; and
c) File appropriate charges against her for failure to perform her duties honestly and diligently and to present the missing funds upon demand.
Furthermore, the Municipal Mayor designate a responsible liquidating officer and see to it that he/she shall be closely supervised by the Municipal Mayor to ensure that the new liquidating officer deposits all his/her collections intact daily or not later than the next banking day as required under Section 69 of PD 1445, and related COA issuance, and to avoid commission of similar shortages and/or occurrence of risks of loss of public funds.

Management Comment:

The Municipal Mayor had instructed the Human Resource Officer to submit the needed
reports and documents as soon as possible.

